The breakfast of champions. Simone Biles has 32 medals to her name, seven National All-around titles, and four gymnastics skills named after her. She is at the top of her game. But getting to where she is today required resilience, determination, and the support of a loving family. Born with boundless energy and a heart filled with love, Simone's childhood environment was a challenges she spent the early years of her life in foster care. Yet, she never let her circumstances define who she was or where she wanted to go in life. At the age of six, she was adopted and her courage to soar took off. My mom and dad always emphasized to me that it doesn't matter where you come from, it just matters where you go with it, and, to this day, always encourage me to be the best Simone that I can be. It is my hope that my journey can be an inspiration to others, to pursue their own dreams and not to wait until you reach your goals to be proud of yourself, but rather be proud of the steps you take toward reaching your goals in life. Simone credits her success to a combination of hard work, dedication, setting goals and the power of dreams. And today, she is determined to help give more children the chance to find their passions and gain access to the resources they need to pursue their dreams. She works with Friends of the Children, a national non-profit that matches youth who face great obstacles with paid, professional mentors. And she is committed to inspiring the next generation of girls everywhere to feel comfortable and confident and to chase their dreams through her Athleta Girl clothing line and with the support of Athleta's Power of the Fund. In recognition of her efforts as an advocate for mental health and a committed supporter of this country's next generation, Simone was awarded the highest honor an American civilian can receive: the Presidential Medal of Freedom in July 2022. At age 25, she is the youngest person ever to receive the Presidential Medal of Freedom. Simone Biles doesn't let any of her life circumstances define who she is as a person and she's on a mission to empower kids all over the world to be the best version of themselves. She's a leader. She's an advocate. She's a champion. Photo credit: Allison cheng. Friends of the children. This package is sold by weight, not volume.
